The paper discusses improving the interpretability of tree-based machine learning models, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also applies these tools to medical machine learning problems, which could fall under the category of computational epidemiology (cs.CE) or cryptography and security (cs.CR) if the focus is on protecting patient privacy. Additionally, the paper discusses monitoring a machine learning model deployed in a hospital, which could fall under the category of databases (cs.DB) if the focus is on data management.
